  <brief_title>PDE5 Inhibitor Use and Non-arteritic Anterior Ischemic Optic Neuropathy (NAION)</brief_title>
  <official_title>Prospective Case Crossover Study to Assess Whether PDE5 Inhibitor Exposure in Men With Erectile Dysfunction Increases the Risk for the Development of Non-arteritic Anterior Ischemic Optic Neuropathy (NAION)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Bayer</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Bayer</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
    <is_fda_regulated_drug>Yes</is_fda_regulated_drug>
    <is_fda_regulated_device>No</is_fda_regulated_device>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of this study is to determine whether the use of PDE5 inhibitors
      (vardenafil, sildenafil, or tadalafil) increases the risk for the development of NAION.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Collected data will be compared to historic data of the same participant in case-crossover
      design.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
